      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks for the list. I think the \"timing differences\" or \"misplaced items\" might be the most likely. \n\nQuick follow up: if we find out it's actually a system error—like the software isn't registering every single movement perfectly—how do we distinguish between a legitimate software bug and something more manual, like someone just forgetting to scan an item out? Is there a standard way to audit that?",
